Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 207
S.P. 96 In Senate, January 14, 2025
Cash Under the Maine Clean Election Act
Reference to the Committee on Veterans and Legal Affairs suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BENNETT of Oxford.
Cosponsored by Representative ARATA of New Gloucester and
Senators: CYRWAY of Kennebec, GROHOSKI of Hancock, HICKMAN of Kennebec,
Representatives: GRAHAM of North Yarmouth, MALON of Biddeford.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §1125, sub-§3, ¶F, as enacted by PL 2019, c. 323, §29, is
3 amended to read:
4 F. A contributor may make a qualifying contribution to a participating candidate in the
5 form of cash, as long as the contributor signs a form prepared by the commission
6 affirming that the contributor made the contribution with personal funds. A candidate
7 receiving qualifying contributions in cash shall submit the contributions to the
8 commission in the aggregate in the form of a cashier's check or money order payable
9 to the fund. The candidate may not deposit qualifying contributions received in cash
10 into the candidate's campaign account.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill eliminates the requirement that contributors making qualifying contributions
1133 in the form of cash to a participating candidate in the Maine Clean Election Act sign a form
1144 affirming that the contributor made the contribution with personal funds.
